    {
      "id": "328f102a82f48278abff35afb598f3a4b8067e74",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2013-01-30 04:30:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nI think this is a terrible idea.\nWe still need to ensure clients are able to do io in absense of MDS (otherwise we got a single point of failure for the entire cluster).\nSo this test must remain.\nIt may just need to be changed to ensure the client has necessary layout lock before killing off MDS.\n\nThe only way we can land this in this state if it severely affects othr testing, and then on the condition that somebody will start working on a proper test fix right away for a very soon submission.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "23af032d7de3eaff5608f702015244fd3c9cd211",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-08 05:39:12.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: No score\n\nOk, we went though the actual failure with Jinshan.\n\nThe failure is not because the connection is lost, the failure is because the MDT is actually alive, and client succesfully reconnected, now due to bz 16774 we are dropping all unused locks on reconnect.\n\nThe test itself has a problem - it only expects a single client present so when the connect request is dropped, there's now no from what client would the request be dropped, from the io making one or some other possibly present clients.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "ec0af98bbf817b98a7997578ff57f92e86f76004",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-08 05:39:13.000000000",
      "message": "Change has been successfully cherry-picked as 945a97dbc2f0323352950d3b54beda9f7ab799a7.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    }
  ],
